fields.manuscript_full_text_std_spelling: Dixit dominus
fields.indexing_notes: Rubric: cum caeteris. Although this chant has only the incipit of the melody, the beginning corresponds to the full rendering of "Dixit dominus" at 37v, within the ferial office, "Dom. per annum". This is also where the full sequence of antiphons is recorded, with various references later in the manuscript to only the first antiphon in the sequence.
